{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κονί-α</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> and <i>Epic dialect</i> <b>κονίη</b>, ἡ, (κόνις): <br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> <b>dust</b>, ποδῶν ὑπένερθε κ. ἵστατ᾽ ἀειρομένη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.150; ὑπὸ δέ σφισιν ὦρτο κ. 11.151: in _plural_, κὰδ δ᾽ ἔπεσ᾽ ἐν κονίῃσι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.98; ἐν κονίῃσι πεσών 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.315, etc.; πρηνέες ἐν κονίῃσιν 2.418, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 365; μιάνθησαν δὲ ἔθειραι αἵματι καὶ κονίῃσι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.796: also Trag. in Lyric poetry, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 64, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 112, “Supp.” 821. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>sand</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.271. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>ashes</b>, in <i>plural</i>, κατ᾽ ἄρ᾽ ἕζετ᾽ ἐπ᾽ ἐσχάρῃ ἐν κονίῃσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.153, compare 160: _sing._, κ. δρυΐνη “Geoponica” 13.4.2. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>pearl-ash, lye, soap-powder</b>, λούειν ἄνευ κονίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 470 (with a play on ἀκονιτί),compare “Ach.” 18, “Ra.” 711, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 430b: _plural_, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.10.4 (nisi to be read κονιάσεις). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>alkaline fluid</b> used for washing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 12.35, +others; κ. στακτή [prev. author] 13.569. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> κ. ἀπὸ τῆς ἱερᾶς σποδοῦ καὶ τοῦ ἱεροῦ ὕδατος, as a medicine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1171.12 (from Lebena). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ={τίτανος}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Erotianus Grammaticus \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] s.<i>Hymns of </i>see.; κ. ἄσβεστος <b>quicklime</b>, Heraclid.<i>Tarentum dialect</i> cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 12.958; κ. μέλαινα “IG” 22.1672.197. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>plaster, stucco</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]42(1).103.278 (Epid.), “POxy.” 1450.4 (3rd c.AD), 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 382.36. [8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus uses ῐ in the quadrisyllabic case κονίῃσι, ῑ in the _trisyllable_: Trag. and Comedy texts ῐ in Lyric poetry (dact. and _anapaest meter_), 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 64, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 112, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 711 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ῑ in <i>iambic</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ach.” 18, “Lys.” 470.] \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8062","accentedUnicode":"κονία","shortDef":"lime; powder","mediumDef":"lime; powder","stepGloss":"lime","stepTransliteration":"konia","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}